      • ArchitectureGenerator

        public ArchitectureGenerator​(int numberOfComponents,
                             int numberOfRequiredFunctions,
                             int adaptabilityDegree)

        Creates a generator with random seed.

        Parameters:
        numberOfComponents - number of components in the generated architecture.
        numberOfRequiredFunctions - number of functions (services) that every component must require.
        adaptabilityDegree - how many times every component should be duplicated.

      • ArchitectureGenerator

        public ArchitectureGenerator​(int numberOfComponents,
                             int numberOfRequiredFunctions,
                             int adaptabilityDegree,
                             long seed)

        Creates a generator with a specified seed.

        Use this constructor if you want to generate again a previously generated architecture.

        Parameters:
        numberOfComponents - number of components in the generated architecture.
        numberOfRequiredFunctions - number of functions (services) that every component must require.
        adaptabilityDegree - how many times every component should be duplicated.
        seed - seed for the random generation.
